:QUOTE
A great local food blog is a love letter to a place written one meal at a time.

:INFO
Local Restaurant Review Blog
Start a restaurant review blog with a consistent voice, decent photos, and local SEO muscle. Pick one metro area or neighborhood and cover it completely before expanding.

:COUNTER.half
2 Reviews
Minimum weekly publishing cadence to build authority
|
:COUNTER.half
6 Months
Time to first meaningful organic search traffic

:PATH
Write the Reviews
Develop a consistent review structure: ambiance, service, dishes ordered, standout items, and a verdict. Visit twice before publishing if budget allows. Be honest without being cruel.

:PATH
Photograph the Food
Use natural light whenever possible. Sit near a window. Shoot from above or at a 45-degree angle. Edit in Lightroom or Snapseed. One strong hero image is worth more than ten mediocre ones.

:PATH
Grow the Audience
Target long-tail local search terms like best tacos in [neighborhood]. Build an email list from day one. Post to local foodie Facebook groups. Tag restaurants on Instagram with location tags.

:CHECKLIST
Launch Checklist
[ ] Choose a blog name that includes the city or neighborhood
[ ] Set up WordPress with a clean food-focused theme
[ ] Write 10 reviews before launch to establish credibility
[ ] Install Rank Math or Yoast for local SEO
[ ] Create an Instagram account and link to the blog
[ ] Set up Google Search Console and submit sitemap
[ ] Join local foodie Facebook groups and introduce yourself

:NOTE
Disclose any comped meals or press dinners clearly and immediately. Reader trust is the only real asset a review blog has, and it takes years to build and seconds to destroy.
